content.raw: Looks good. There is still console output when the verbose level is set to 0, 1, or 2. A value of zero should have no output, 1=error, 2=error\+warning, 3=error\+warning\+info, 4=error\+warning\+info\+debug. I think the pretty print of “Downloading model: ….” should only appear on levels 3 and 4.
